# 📱 BudgetCap Mobile App — Implementation Plan
### Stack: Expo · NativeWind · TypeScript

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The mobile app will consume the **existing Next.js API routes** as a backend. No server code needs to be rewritten — only the frontend becomes React Native.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Expo App<br/>NativeWind + TypeScript] -->|HTTP / REST| B[Next.js API Routes<br/>Deployed on Vercel]
    B --> C[(PostgreSQL<br/>via Prisma)]
    A --> D[Expo SecureStore<br/>JWT Session Token]
    A --> E[React Query<br/>Cache + Sync]
```

The app is a **separate package** inside a pnpm monorepo (already configured via `pnpm-workspace.yaml`). It calls the deployed Next.js API directly — no code sharing of server-only modules.

---

